<br>
This leads me to believe 2 things:<br>
<br>
1.  The reduction scales lower on small casting spells.  Makes sense, don't want a spell to become essentially free, same as not wanting fast casting spell to become nearly instantaneous.<br>
<br>
2.  The earring does reduce mana useage.  Every single time, with every single spell I tried that the earring glowed on, I was able to cast more times with the earring than without.<br>
<br>
The number of times with and without was also consistent.  The earring does reduce mana useage.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 479<br> <font color=#333333>(3/22/02 7:14:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Earring Test</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Specialization is TOTALLY random it is not fixed, its easy to see.<br>
