No, it isn't.  I ran some very detailed tests (which I think are stored off in the library forum on www.graffe.com) which show the savings is on every single cast and is equal to your specialization skill divided by 17.5.  So with 200 specialization, you save 200/17.5 ~= 11.43%.  Your 50 specializes save 50/17.5 ~= 2.86%.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure where the 17.5 came from, it may have had something to do with my level and my int.  I only know that at level 57 with the stats I had, the constant was 17.5 (or 1750 if you prefer decimals over percentages).<br>
<br>
I gather the ShowEQ folks have had similar results.<br>
<br>
Twiddle O`Toole<br>
59 Wizard / Veeshan<br>
