<br>
When I ran the test with the earring, I took off one of my bracers and wore no otehr focus items.  When I did the test without the earring, I put on the focus bracer to keep my mana pool constant.  There's little doubt about the bracer's effect at this point, so I figured it was a safe swap.  <br>
<br>
I ran the test with Scars of Sigil.<br>
I ran the test with Blaze.<br>
I ran the test with Dismiss Summoned.<br>
<br>
All showed a roughly 10% savings with the earring worn.  With Scars, I got 21 casts per full bar of mana with the earring on, and 19 without the earring.  I have the data for the others at home, and I'm at work, but I'll post the results when I get home.  <br>
<br>
All of these spells are damage-type spells.  I'll run the test with malise tomorrow.  I'm specialized on conjuration, so I've been avoiding conjur spells for my tests.   <p><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res0n86l/maesig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 482<br> <font color=#333333>(3/23/02 10:58:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1153.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Earring Test</span><hr size=1> Shouldn't help with Malise.  It only glows for DD's and DoT's.  I suppose it could save mana on Malise anyways, but it doesn't glow.  /shrug <p>~~
